                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1322">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.93/20.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-02T11:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 2, 1912—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Protection of Chinese, your April 29, 9 p.m. If the Mexican Government makes no
                    objection, the consular agent at Cananea may exert his unofficial good offices
                    in every proper way to secure protection of the Chinese in that district. You
                    will so inform him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
